==English==
===Etymology===
The first three letters of the Latin alphabet, standing for the whole alphabet

===Noun===
'''ABC''' (''plural'' '''ABCs''')

#(''US also'' '''ABCs'''; ''uncountable'') The [[alphabet]].
#:''Do you know your ABCs?'' 
#(''obsolete'') A primer for teaching the [[Latin alphabet]] and first elements of reading. 
#(''not used in the plural'') The simplest rudiments of any subject.
#''the '''ABC''' of finance''

====Synonyms====
*(''rudiments''): [[basic]]s, [[fundamental]]s, [[rudiment]]s

